num_tested_probands: The report discusses a single 31-year-old male patient who was referred to the movement disorders outpatient clinic.
A clinical presentation of a single 31-year-old patient was described.
num_positive_het_probands: No probands were reported to have a heterozygous pathogenic variant. The report focuses on biallelic variants, not heterozygous conditions.
There is no mention of heterozygous probands in the case report.
positive_phenotypes: The patient presented with severe hyperkinetic movement disorder, dystonia, chorea, ballism, and cognitive deficits, as described in the clinical presentation.
The clinical presentation described includes 'severe hyperkinetic movement disorder', 'uncontrollable dystonic and ballistic movements', 'nonverbal communication with parents', and 'react to orders'.
num_compound_or_double_hets: The patient had compound heterozygous variants in WARS2: one inherited maternally (c.149G>A p.GlySOAsp) and the other paternally (c.37T>G, p.(Trp13Gly)).
The report mentions 'biallelic variants in WARS2 encoding mitochondrial tryptophanyl-tRNA synthase in six individuals with mitochondrial encephalopathy'.
